description:
Born in Naples on August 23, 1983, he graduated in 2002 at the Art School of Cardito (Italy). He studied for 3 years at the "Italian School of Comix" of Naples (2005/2008). He realized between 2007 and 2008 two street posters for the "National Campagn for the Defence of Dogs" regarding abandonment issue. In 2008 he was also selected from "RedWhale Studio" (by Katja Centomo and Francesco Artibani) to develop a tutoring comic. In July 2009, he made one comic issue for the magazine "Evil comics". In 2010, he created a series of illustrations for the pictured books "Pop Pixie".

He also made two pages for the comic event "Nero Napoletano" in collaboration with the "Italian School of Comix" of Naples, in the same period he's been classified first place in the contest "Imago" along with Francesca Carotenuto with whom he formed an artistic and professional duo. He is now working on the project "The Case of Orion - The Key of Zaphura" (I Casi di Orione - La Chiave di Zaphura) for the italian publisher "In Form of Art Press" with Francesca Carotenuto (story and text) and Mariacristina Federico (colors).
